The paper deals with wireless relay networks and their capacity, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of linear network coding and quantization also suggests the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of digital-to-analog and analog-to-digital converters, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the connection between network coding for wireline networks and codes for Gaussian networks, which suggests the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
